      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RUBY JUAN (2) produced a moderate run last time when fifth at this track over 388m behind Federal Senor (22.68) in a Grade 3/4. Was in the money the start prior. Form from her last run is proving strong. Looks the one to beat on her best form. PITMAN GO WELL (4) finished in the placings last time but could not have been more impressive three back in his strong 22.30 win at this track over 388m. Has the ability and looks a key chance. NOVA LASS (3) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 4 lengths at this track in a handy 22.39 beating Chief Enforcer. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Leading player again. BRAVE CHOICE (1) is a last start winner worth following up.",
